Solution 1:
------------------using loop------------------------- 
def palindrome(s):
  n=len(s)
  for i in range(n):
    if s[i] !=s[n-i-1]:
      return False
    return True
s="nitin"
print(palindrome(s))

Solution 2:
-------------------using split method --------------------
def palindrome(s):
  temp=s[::-1]
  if s==temp:
    print("It is a plaindrome number")
  else:
    print("It is not a palindrome number")
s="aman"
palindrome(s)

